HEADWORD: collectivized
<hw>col*lec"tiv*ized</hw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>brought under collective
ownership and operating under collectivist principles; -- used
especially of organizations operating under the ownership by the
state.</def> <note>[Narrower terms: <stype>socialistic (vs.
capitalistic), socialist</stype>; <stype>communistic</stype>]</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> collective, collectivised,
state-controlled.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

